Key Match Events: Emilio Nsue scored a hat-trick for Equatorial Guinea with goals in the 21st, 51st, and 64th minutes.
Josete Miranda scored for Equatorial Guinea in the 47th minute.
Esteban Orozco scored an own goal for Guinea-Bissau in the 1st half.
Jefferson Encada scored for Guinea-Bissau in the 95th minute.
VAR was used to confirm Jefferson Encada's goal for Guinea-Bissau.
Luis Asue (Equatorial Guinea) received a yellow card.
Saul Coco (Equatorial Guinea) received a yellow card and conceded a penalty.
Pre-Game Insights: Equatorial Guinea came into the match with an 11-game unbeaten run.
Guinea-Bissau was looking for its first win in the history of the Africa Cup of Nations.
Equatorial Guinea's probable line-up included Owono, Akapo, Anieboh, Orozco, Ndong, Ganet, Bikoro, Miranda, Machin, Salvador, and Nsue.
Guinea-Bissau's probable line-up included Mendes, Cande, Sori Mané, Djaló, Carlos Mané, Semedo, Cassama, Rodrigues, Quizera, Gano, and Balde.
Post-Match Reflections: Equatorial Guinea beat Guinea-Bissau 4-2 in the second round of the African Cup of Nations.
Emilio Nsue is the all-time leading scorer for Equatorial Guinea with 17 goals.
Guinea-Bissau has yet to win a match in the Africa Cup of Nations.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match took place at the Alassane Ouattara Olympic Stadium in Abidjan, Ivory Coast.
The match had 8 minutes of extra time.
The match was streamed on Bandplay.
